    "John Trapp": "And bringeth forth herbs ] So the fruitful Christian (that, watered with the word and Spirit, bringeth forth a harvest of holiness) shall receive the blessing of increase, #Joh 15:2 . Such trees as brought forth fruit fit for meat were not to be destroyed, #De 20:19 ; but trees that were not for fruit were for the fire, #Mt 3:10 . The earth thankfully returns her burden to the painful tiller. Let earth teach earth: terram quam terimus, terram quam gerimus, the earth we tear, the earth we bear.\nVer.\n7. And bringeth forth herbs] So the fruitful Christian (that, watered with the word and Spirit, bringeth forth a harvest of [v_Jhn_15_2] holiness) shall receive the blessing of increase, #Joh 15:\n7. That passage, \"As thy soul liveth,\" is not an oath, but an asseveration, or obtestation only, conjoined with the oath. An end of all strife] The end of an oath is to help the truth in [v_Exo_22_11] necessity, and to clear men\u2019s innocency, #Ex 22:"
